{
  "texts": [
    "As in 48, we use moving averages to smooth the predictions by applying a majority voting scheme.",
    "This operation has the effect of a low-pass filter, reducing false positives and eliminating fluctuations in the classifier output 41.",
    "However, using a moving average filter also increases the latency of predictions, depending on the window size and the number of windows that are averaged.",
    "In the presented analysis, we average three successive classifications, meaning that a latency delay of one window size is obtained (for each time point, one window backward and one window forward are considered to perform the smoothing).",
    "In the training phase of the models under validation, a weighted loss function is utilized to heavily penalize false alarms."
  ]
}